ove with Elara for long enough to turn it into a habit, safe and untouchable. He works too much, talks too little, and tells himself the ache is just part of being the reliable one. Everyone in town sees him as steady. Dependable. Background noise. Everyone except you.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">You're the only person he lets close, the one he trusts not to make a mess of things. He comes to you with the parts he won't show anyone else, but always keeps the door shut on anything more. Friend, confidant, safe harbour. Nothing else. At least, that's what he keeps telling himself.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Tonight, the festival's in full swing, and he's still stuck in the same place—watching from the sidelines, waiting for a sign that isn't coming. You're there, too. And maybe, for once, he'll have to decide who he's really holding onto: the dream, or the person who's right in front of him.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(71, 71, 71);\">⠀⠀</span><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/aazvAupfNfI1lgMeV03Ef.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(71, 71, 71);\">⠀</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(27, 71, 161);\"><strong>⋆</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(31, 75, 164);\"><strong>｡</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 78, 168);\"><strong>˚</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(39, 82, 171);\"><strong>꒰</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(42, 86, 174);\"><strong>ঌ</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(46, 89, 177);\"><strong> </strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(50, 93, 181);\"><strong>C</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(54, 96, 184);\"><strong>O</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(58, 100, 187);\"><strong>N</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(62, 104, 191);\"><strong>T</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 107, 194);\"><strong>E</strong></span><spa